ol)>)\n-> BTreeMap<&'a N, (BTreeSet<&'a T>, bool)>","parent":null,"children":[],"decl_id":null,"docs":" Compute the FOLLOW sets of the grammar.\n Returns a map mapping from nonterminal to (follow set, whether follow set contains EOF)\n","sig":null,"attributes":[{"value":"/ Compute the FOLLOW sets of the grammar.","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":12009,"byte_end":12052,"line_start":325,"line_end":325,"column_start":5,"column_end":48}},{"value":"/ Returns a map mapping from nonterminal to (follow set, whether follow set contains EOF)","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":12057,"byte_end":12148,"line_start":326,"line_end":326,"column_start":5,"column_end":96}}]},{"kind":"Method","id":{"krate":0,"index":71},"span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":15031,"byte_end":15036,"line_start":386,"line_end":386,"column_start":12,"column_end":17},"name":"lalr1","qualname":"<Grammar<T, N, A>>::lalr1","value":"pub fn lalr1<'a, FR, FO>(&'a Self, FR, FO)\n-> Result<LR1ParseTable, LR1Conflict> where\nFR: FnMut(&Rhs<T, N, A>, Option<&T>) -> bool,\nFO: FnMut(&Rhs<T, N, A>, Option<&T>) -> i32","parent":null,"children":[],"decl_id":null,"docs":" Try to create an LALR(1) parse table out of the grammar.","sig":null,"attributes":[{"value":"/ Try to create an LALR(1) parse table out of the grammar.","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":14063,"byte_end":14123,"line_start":373,"line_end":373,"column_start":5,"column_end":65}},{"value":"/","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":14128,"byte_end":14131,"line_start":374,"line_end":374,"column_start":5,"column_end":8}},{"value":"/ You can tweak the behaviour of the parser in two ways:","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":14136,"byte_end":14194,"line_start":375,"line_end":375,"column_start":5,"column_end":63}},{"value":"/","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":14199,"byte_end":14202,"line_start":376,"line_end":376,"column_start":5,"column_end":8}},{"value":"/ - `reduce_on` is a predicate, allowing you to control certain reduce rules based on the","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":14207,"byte_end":14298,"line_start":377,"line_end":377,"column_start":5,"column_end":96}},{"value":"/   lookahead token. This function takes two parameters: the rule, given by its right-hand","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":14303,"byte_end":14395,"line_start":378,"line_end":378,"column_start":5,"column_end":97}},{"value":"/   side, and the lookahead token (or `None` for EOF). You can use this to resolve","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":14400,"byte_end":14484,"line_start":379,"line_end":379,"column_start":5,"column_end":89}},{"value":"/   shift-reduce conflicts. For example, you can solve the \"dangling else\" problem by","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":14489,"byte_end":14576,"line_start":380,"line_end":380,"column_start":5,"column_end":92}},{"value":"/   forbidding the reduce action on an `else` token.","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":14581,"byte_end":14635,"line_start":381,"line_end":381,"column_start":5,"column_end":59}},{"value":"/ - `priority_of` allows you to resolve reduce-reduce conflicts, by giving reduce rules","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":14640,"byte_end":14729,"line_start":382,"line_end":382,"column_start":5,"column_end":94}},{"value":"/   different \"priorities\". This takes the same parameters as `reduce_on`, so you can vary","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":14734,"byte_end":14826,"line_start":383,"line_end":383,"column_start":5,"column_end":97}},{"value":"/   the priority based on the lookahead token. If there would be a reduce-reduce conflict","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":14831,"byte_end":14922,"line_start":384,"line_end":384,"column_start":5,"column_end":96}},{"value":"/   between rules, but they have different priority, the one with higher priority is used.","span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":14927,"byte_end":15019,"line_start":385,"line_end":385,"column_start":5,"column_end":97}}]},{"kind":"Method","id":{"krate":0,"index":82},"span":{"file_name":"/Users/pepijnvanderklei/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/lalr-0.0.2/src/lib.rs","byte_start":22133,"byte_end":22149,"line_start":537,"line_end":537,"column_start":12,"column_end":28},"name":"extended_grammar","qualname":"<LR0StateMachine>::extended_grammar","value":"pub fn extended_grammar(&Self)\n-> Grammar<&'a T, (usize, &'a N), (usize, &'a Rhs<T, N, A>)>","parent":null,"children":[],"decl_id":null,"docs":" Create an LALR(1) extended grammar, as described\n [here](http://web.cs.dal.ca/~sjackson/lalr1.html).\n","sig":null,"attributes":[